Indeed, also ep.1 is problematic. However, it seems to work fine on my DivX Player. Overall, the quality of this season sucks (no offence, uploader). Ugly TVRips and mpeg encoding.

Read here how you should handle ep. 01 and 07 to make them work:
1. Check Google/Yahoo for a free application called NanDub binary (it is a .exe file, no need to install). Open nandub.exe. 
2. From the "File" box, press "open the video file". In the "open" box tick "Popup extended open options" and then select your episode and press "open". In the new opened window tick first box, "Re-derive keyframe flags" and then press OK. NanDub will start now rekeying video stream. It will take about 5 minutes.
2. When finished rekeying, in the "Video" box tick "Direct Stream Copy"; in the "Audio" box tick "Direct Stream Copy" and "AVI audio". Open "Interleaving" and set Preload=0, in stead of 500, and tick "frames", not "ms".
3. In the "File" box "Save as AVI".
The whole thing should take about 10 minutes. It worked for me so it will work for you either. Good luck.
